cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques for sentiment analysis of text documents written in Macedonian language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves feature selection and classification, which are common topics in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for sentiment analysis falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves analysis of online forums, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
